Merge: Combine changes from one branch into another while keeping history.
Rebase: Move your branch on top of another branch to make history linear.
Squash: Combine multiple commits into a single commit.
Stash: Temporarily save uncommitted changes and clean your working directory.
Reset: Undo commits and move back to a previous state (optionally keeping changes).
Revert: Undo a commit by creating a new commit that reverses it.
Fetch: Get latest changes from remote without merging them.
Push: Send your local commits to the remote repository.
Pull: Fetch + merge changes from remote into your local branch
